\begin_layout Standard

\family roman
\size normal
Before discussing the measurement process and the manifestations of nonlocality
 and contextuality in discrete quantum mechanics, we first review various
 notations brought forward from conventional quantum theory.
 Assume that a physical system is represented by a state 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{\Psi}$
\end_inset

, and that we wish to measure a physical quantity 
\begin_inset Formula ${\cal O}$
\end_inset

 of this system, with corresponding observable 
\begin_inset Formula ${\mathbf{O}}$
\end_inset

, whose eigenspectrum is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
{\mathbf{O}}\left|i\right\rangle =\lambda_{i}\left|i\right\rangle \ .
\]

\end_inset

Then the Born rule of CQT tells us that the probability of obtaining the
 eigenvalue 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{i}$
\end_inset

 as an outcome of the measurement is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\begin{array}{rcccl}
{\cal P}_{\Psi}\left(\lambda_{i}\right) & = & {\displaystyle {\frac{\langle\Psi|{P}_{i}|\Psi\rangle}{\ip{\Psi}{\Psi}}}} & = & {\displaystyle {\frac{\ip{\Psi}{i}\ip{i}{\Psi}}{\ip{\Psi}{\Psi}\ip{i}{i}}}}\end{array}\ ,\label{prob1.eq}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula ${P}_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the projector onto the subspace generated by the eigenvector 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|i\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
 We have until now assumed non-degenerate eigenvalues.
 If, for some set of states 
\begin_inset Formula $\{k\}$
\end_inset

, the eigenvalue 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

 is degenerate, we account for that by replacing the simple expression for
 the projector 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{i}$
\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P_{\lambda}=\sum_{k=1}^{K_{\lambda}}\frac{\left|k\right\rangle \left\langle k\right|}{\ip{k}{k}}\ ,
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $K_{\lambda}$
\end_inset

 is the degeneracy of the eigenvalue 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

